ui-rs.settings.autoResponder.autoRespond:
Affects: Supply

  • On: The cancellation auto-responder will automatically approve cancellation requests if the item has not yet shipped.
  • Off: All cancellation requests must receive a manual response.

Affects: Supply

The auto-responder will respond to new requests based on a real-time availability check of your local ILS. If there is at least one available item, the auto-responder will respond “expects to supply.” If there are no available items, it will respond “Cannot supply.”

  • On for found items: If there is at least one available item, the auto-responder will respond “expects to supply.”
  • On auto not found: If there is at least one available item, the auto-responder will respond “expects to supply.” AND if there are no available items, it will respond “Cannot supply.”

Libraries quite often do not work on weekends when supplying material to other libraries, so if we do not exclude weekends when determining if a request is stale ot not the request may become stale before the supplying library has had a chance to look at the request
